# Mandatory agent compliance

**Binding:** Every rule in `.cursor/rules/` applies to this repository — **every session, every task type, no exceptions.** Do not skip, summarize away, override, or treat rules as optional based on scope (“small fix”, “quick question”, “docs only”, “just reviewing”). When in doubt, **read the full rule file** with the Read tool before proceeding.

> **The rules exist to keep architecture, i18n, tests, security, UX, and release discipline in check.** Skipping them is a merge blocker equivalent to a failing CI build.

## No task is exempt

| Task type | Rules still apply |
|-----------|-------------------|
| Implementation / feature / bug fix | **All** always-apply rules + scoped rules for touched paths |
| Code review / PR feedback | `review-commit.mdc`, `architecture-clean.mdc`, `qa-testing.mdc`, scoped rules for changed paths |
| Question / explanation (“how does X work?”) | Answer must respect documented architecture and conventions; read scoped rules if the answer touches that layer |
| Test-only / CI fix | `qa-testing.mdc`, `ci-cd.mdc`, `delivery-workflow.mdc` |
| Docs / rules / workflow edits | `delivery-workflow.mdc`, `review-commit.mdc`; keep `AGENTS.md` index in sync |
| Commit / PR / merge / release | `review-commit.mdc`, `ci-cd.mdc`, `version-management.mdc` |
| Refactor / dependency bump | All always-apply rules + `kmp-core.mdc`, `official-docs-urls.mdc` |

**Never** assume a rule does not apply because the diff is small or the user did not mention it.

