## Task-start checklist (agents) — required every session

1. **Acknowledge compliance** — this task follows `.cursor/rules/`; no rule will be skipped for convenience.
2. **Classify task** — implementation, review, test-only, docs, release, question.
3. **Identify release phase** per `version-management.mdc` — branch, CI track, `version.prerelease`; adapt scope (alpha iteration vs beta freeze vs prod hotfix).
4. **Inventory applicable rules** — list always-apply set + any scoped rules for paths you will read, edit, or review.
5. **Read scoped rules** — use the Read tool on every matching scoped rule **before** writing code or giving review verdicts.
6. **Plan** per `delivery-workflow.mdc` — layers, i18n, tests, QA YAML.
7. **Implement** using `architecture-clean`, `kmp-core`, `ui-ux-compose`, `i18n-multilingual`.
8. **Test** per `qa-testing.mdc` — run Gradle tasks before claiming done (when code changed).
9. **Self-review** per `review-commit.mdc` before PR/commit.
10. **CI/release** per `ci-cd.mdc` when pushing or releasing.

## Task-end checklist (before "done")

- [ ] **All applicable rules consulted** — always-apply set + scoped rules for touched paths; none skipped
- [ ] Layer boundaries respected (no UI in domain/data; no `*Impl` in composables)
- [ ] All new strings in **8** locale `strings.xml` files
- [ ] Journey components / semantic colors (no raw Material forms or one-off hex)
- [ ] **New functionality has unit tests** — every new domain method, screen model transition, codec, or repository method has a corresponding `*Test.kt` covering happy path + edge cases (`qa-testing.mdc` coverage table)
- [ ] **Existing tests updated** — every test that exercises changed code compiles, passes, and reflects the new behavior; no stale assertions left behind
- [ ] **Fakes kept in sync** — all `Fake*` and `Instrumented*Fakes` implement the full current interface; no `TODO()` stubs introduced
- [ ] `:composeApp:testDebugUnitTest` runs green (`BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, zero failures) — when Kotlin changed
- [ ] `:composeApp:compileDebugAndroidTestKotlinAndroid` compiles clean — when UI or fakes changed
- [ ] `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml` updated if user-facing flows changed
- [ ] No secrets committed; commit only if user explicitly asked

## Reviews & commits

- **Code review:** Use `review-commit.mdc` priority table (P0 security → P4 style). Reviews must cite rule violations by rule file name.
- **Commits:** Only when user asks; message explains **why**; never skip hooks.
- **PRs:** Test plan required; wait for CI green before merge.

## Anti-patterns (compliance failures)

- “Small change” → skipping tests, i18n, or architecture rules
- Answering architecture questions without reading `architecture-clean.mdc`
- Touching `supabase/**` without reading `supabase-backend.mdc` and relevant skills
- Implementing UI without `ui-ux-compose.mdc` and `i18n-multilingual.mdc`
- Claiming done without Gradle gates when code changed
- Replacing project rules with generic LLM best practices

